    "narrative": "For the April 13th slate, the Zurich Zebras lean heavily on the top of the lineup to drive production, headlined by **Trea Turner** (81.27) and **Kyle Schwarber** (79.42). Both benefit significantly from a favorable matchup against Javier Assad, whose 4.83 xERA presents an ideal target for our power-speed stack. **Trea Turner** is the clear anchor today; his elite position in the leadoff spot combined with the wind blowing out results in a premium 81.27 efficiency score. **Kyle Schwarber** also sees a massive boost, with his 0.402 xwOBA providing a high ceiling against a pitcher he should capitalize on. **Josh Smith** also warrants attention; despite being slotted in the bottom third of the lineup, his strong 62.54 score is bolstered by a 15% SP skill advantage against Luis Severino and a favorable park factor, making him a high-value start in the 1B slot.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involves **Carson Benge**, who just missed the cut with a 36.52 score. While his base projection was respectable, the combination of a tough matchup against Justin Wrobleski (2.89 xERA) and the optimizer\u2019s prioritization of lineup position effectively pushed him to the bench. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (42.34) and **Hyeseong Kim** (45.73); while both are technically above the floor, their scores are dampened by unfavorable platoons and low lineup spots. We must remain vigilant, as **Logan O'Hoppe**, **Caleb Durbin**, and **Victor Scott II** are also currently subject to \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions. Should **Caleb Durbin** drop in the order or if the weather impact at his venue shifts, we may need to pivot. Given the scarcity of SB, the presence of **Victor Scott II** and **Trea Turner** remains critical to our strategy, even if **Victor Scott II** faces a moderate challenge against Gavin Williams.",
